Of course you can “dog-groom” it by dividing by $1-i$. $$\\~\\ \frac{i\left(1-i^{259}\right)}{1-i}$$ [/think] \\~\\ Since $i^{4n+1}=i$, we have $i^{259}=i$, and so the above becomes $\\\frac{-i\left(1+i\right)}{1-i}\\=\frac{-2i}{1-i}\\=\frac{-2i\left(1+i\right)}{\left(1-i\right)\left(1+i\right)}\\=\frac{i-2}{2}$ [/think] Finally, you can rationalize the denominator to get $\dfrac{2-i}{2}$ [/answer]
